Description
The table contains data related to trips conducted by drivers using specific trucks and trailers. 
Key information includes trip identifiers, scheduling details, actual distance traveled, duration of trips, 
fuel consumption, and the status of the trip. This data can be utilized for analyzing driver performance, 
optimizing routes, monitoring fuel efficiency, and understanding operational productivity.

  COLUMN                    |              TYPE                  |      COMMENT      
TRIP_ID                     |             STRING                 |
LOAD_ID                     |             STRING                 |
DRIVER_ID                   |             STRING                 |
TRUCK_ID                    |             STRING                 |
TRAILER_ID                  |             STRING                 |
DISPATCH_DATE               |              DATE                  |
ACTUAL_DISTANCE_MILES       |             BIGINT                 |
ACTUAL_DURATION_HOURS       |             DOUBLE                 |
FUEL_GALLONS_USED           |             DOUBLE                 |
AVERAGE_MPG                 |             DOUBLE                 |
IDLE_TIME_HOURS             |             DOUBLE                 |
TRIP_STATUS                 |             STRING                 |

----SAMPLE DATA
Which trip had the highest fuel efficiency?
---SQL:
      SELECT `trip_id`, `average_mpg`
FROM `datawerhouse1`.`bronze`.`trips`
ORDER BY `average_mpg` DESC
LIMIT 1
----RESULT:
        trip_id	    average_mpg
      TRIP00000528	   7.5





